This paper is primarily focused on the control of surgical robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of optimization algorithms and force feedback, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of impedance control, which is a common technique in control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the proposed framework in laparoscopy and infant surgery, which are both areas of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
